Problem:
class TemperatureControlSystem {
  private int roomTemperature;
  private boolean heaterStatus;
  private boolean windowOpen;

  public TemperatureControlSystem() {
    roomTemperature = 20;
    heaterStatus = false;
    windowOpen = false;
  }

  public void setRoomTemperature(int newTemp) {
    if (windowOpen && !heaterStatus) {
      roomTemperature = newTemp - 5;
    } else if (!windowOpen && heaterStatus) {
      roomTemperature = newTemp + 5;
    } else {
      roomTemperature = newTemp;
    }
  }

  public void toggleHeaterStatus() {
    heaterStatus = !heaterStatus;
    if (heaterStatus) {
      roomTemperature += 5;
    } else {
      roomTemperature -= 5;
    }
  }

  public void toggleWindow() {
    windowOpen = !windowOpen;
    if (windowOpen) {
      roomTemperature -= 5;
    } else {
      roomTemperature += 5;
    }
  }
}",

If we assume the room temperature is increased by an intervention, can we deduce this was caused by toggling the window to closed?
